This year was Extraordinary! 💃🏼 I am grateful for all of the creative opportunities that came my way this year 😀

✨ I moved into my own artist Live/Work apartment in Downtown Vancouver. 
✨ Created a brand new collection of paintings 
✨ Started Teaching as a Continuing Studies Instructor at Emily Carr University of Art & Design 
✨ Attended the Azule Artist Residency in NC
✨ Moved to Los Angeles, CA 🌴
✨ Started my Fashion Design program at Otis College of Art and Design 
✨ Participated in 12 Artist Exhibitions
✨ Had my work published in the Women in Art Series by Goss Magazine 💃🏼 
✨ Interviewed by Discover Abstract Artists 👩‍🎨 
✨ Showed my work at my first art fair - Art Vancouver International Art Fair
✨ Exhibited my work in The Other Art Fair, Virtual Editions at the Brooklyn Expo Center 
✨ Sold over $10K of my artwork
✨ Awarded the Talent Prize Award in a International Juried Art Competition 
✨ Showed my work in London, UK 🇬🇧 
✨ Had my artwork published on @artsy & @artnet 💫

Thank you for everyone that has supported my work this year; for all the collectors, exhibitions, publications, and artist residencies that I participated in. Excited to see what 2023 has in store, as I continue to go after my dreams 🎊

You & I (Forever)

#SelfLove ✨

It has been a lifelong creative vision and dream of attending fashion school, creating a brand, and showing my collection on the runway ✨👗🪡💃🏼

After spending numerous amount of hours researching. One day, I opened @blancheworld website. Right there in black and white, clear as day. It reads: “Fast forward your fashion future. Get runway ready in one year”

My decision to attend this program could not be ever more so clear ✨ Saying “Yes” is all about trusting myself, my intuition, my life’s purpose and soul mission. By going “All In” 🌋

I am elated to announce that I am attending Blanche Macdonald Centre Fashion Design program and for receiving the Presidential Scholarship 🫧 
Here in Vancouver, BC starting this May 2023 ✨ 
Ready to set my dreams on fire 🔥

Nicole Melnicky offers an extraordinary opportunity of one-on-one coaching through her “RISE” program. Learn to transmute your low vibrational thoughts and feelings in order to achieve the life of your dreams by achieving your goals. Start at anytime ✨

I am a Life Coach that specializes in Law of Attraction and Abundance Coaching to manifest the life of you dreams. Often times, you hear the terms “Law of Attraction” and “Abundance” but what does that mean? How do you actually do that?

I bring 10 years of experience in teaching and creative manifestation, to my coaching practice; acquired through my life experiences in cities such as Vancouver, Philadelphia, Toronto, New York, and Los Angeles. I bring my expertise and diverse knowledge of manifestation to my “RISE” coaching sessions. I will work with you so that you can RISE Up and help you achieve your ‘BIGGEST’ goals ⚡️

I dedicate my time to help you set ‘BIG’ Goals and then walk you through the process of actually achieving those goals 💥

Through the effort of individualized one-on-one mentorship, vision board creation, goal setting, scripting, affirmations, and visualization. I walk you through the process of achieving, living, and walking in your true life purpose.

Book a 30 min, 1 hour, or 2 hour coaching session with Nicole Melnicky today!

DM for more info! 😊

Bb’s First Day 🌸✨💅🏼 Starting my Diploma of Fashion Design at Blanche MacDonald Centre 🍓 

#TheFutureofFashion ✨

Life Update: Trusting my inner voice hasn’t always been easy ✨ But the more I focus on what I am doing, my path, and what my vision is. The more clear I get on what I want 🙌🏼

We are taught by society to not listen to that little voice inside of us. Because we have been silenced, suppressed, violated….We are taught to doubt ourselves, instead of trusting ourselves. This is where anxiety festers, transpires and breeds. 

Instead, I have learned that I have to TRUST myself and BELIEVE in myself. 

I LISTEN to my intuition no matter how crazy it may seem. Whether that’s quitting a job or moving city to city. It always leads me in the right direction.

I’ve been feeling more positive these days than I have felt in a long time. I’m excited what my future holds after I finish Blanche 💥💃🏼🐍✂️💅🏼

For me, it’s all about trusting yourself one step at a time. All the little pieces, build up, and there you are at the right place at the right time 💥🌟🙌🏼

"If it's about confidence, then I should attend Blanche" - Nicole Melnicky

This is a statement that I made way before finding the article about Visionary Métis Woman, Blanche Brillion MacDonald whom opened up a renown private institution in Vancouver in 1960.

Just two days ago, I found this article and read about this inspirational and brilliant woman. When "Macdonald first became a model, [she] began to teach modelling, developing a course on self-appreciation that was all about confidence, not looks." 👗

When I read this line something within me deeply resonated within me 💫 My soul led me to Blanche Macdonald Centre for a reason ⚡️ I am so grateful to be studying fashion design at this school and to be building the skills, trust, and more confidence in myself for what I want to do.

Beyond inspired these days on my creative journey and future in fashion 🙌🏼

When I graduated from @moorecollegeart, as much as I loved my Fine Arts major, I had this gut intuition that ”I should have studied Fashion Design” ✨

I had this realization within my first year working at @bootleggerjeans in 2015 when I landed a job as an Assistant Designer position that I thought was a Textile Designer role in the industry 🤷🏼‍♀️ Luckily, I had strong skills in Photoshop and Illustrator, and had a great boss, so I picked up the job pretty quick.

That year working at Bootlegger was greatly inspiring, surrounded by people who loved fashion design and by experiencing Vancouver in a new way. I had the opportunity to envision a completely different career trajectory for myself. 

At that time, I wish I had the knowledge of a fashion designer. Since then I have taken multiple classes at @thecutfashionacademy being taught how to Pattern Draft one-on-one by my friend @claudiademcak 🙏🏼 

I am beyond excited that I am finally an official Fashion Design student @blancheworld 🙌🏼 I heard about this school through lot of my friends that had attended for makeup, fashion design, and fashion marketing. Leading them to successful careers in the industry 🌟 Super inspiring! 

Although I am already busy with projects, I could not be more grateful that I am finally doing this dream and can reflect on how far I have come ✂️✨💃🏼👗

Two years ago, I graduated from OCAD University with my MFA in Interdisciplinary Art, Media, and Design 👩🏼‍🎓 It’s amazing how fast time flies by, because this feels like it was yesterday! 

Today, I’m reflecting on this inspiring time in my life when I spent time developing my first ever LGTBQ+ Pride Fashion Collection 🏳️‍🌈 “Imagining a Queer Utopia” which embodies my Pansexual and Queer identity through colour, digital prints, and eccentric garments. My collection challenges the notions of feminism, gender and sexuality, through potent exaggeration and visceral imagination. To me colour isn’t one dimensional or “superficial.” It’s a multidimensional form that expresses individuality, queer identity, femininity, and pride 🌈 It allows me to express Queerness in a positive light 💫

After graduating OCAD, I spent a year working and teaching art. In the back of my mind, I knew that I wanted to attend Fashion School. I am grateful that I figured out how to manifest it and to make it happen. Grateful to say this past month I started the next stage of my creative journey at Blanche MacDonald’s Fashion Design program ✨

I am proud of Who I Am 🏳️‍🌈💃🏼✨👠 I would never want to change a thing about myself. ‘Cause I’m on the right track, Baby, I was Born This Way!’ 💥

Thrilled to see this article posted on @artsy speaking about Queer Abstraction ✨🌏🏳️‍🌈 Love that this article furthers the dialogue is on queer art and abstraction. Expanding the conversation on queer politics, it states: “In the face of a culture that seeks to label everything, queer abstraction turns its back.” ✊🏻 Labels often divide us. Instead they are supposed to operate differently and do the opposite by bringing us closer to one another. By allowing us “in” ❤️💛💜🧡

Queer Abstraction not only creates a space for non-binary identities, gender and sexuality to be expressed through a fluid free-flowing space 💫 But it opens up the possibilities of queer utopia and futuristism. 

Artists such as Amy Sillman, Carrie Moyer and Helen Frankenthaler and the writing of David J. Getsey and José Esteban Muñoz have always inspired me and have been revolutionary to my studio practice 🪐 Grateful to see this article posted on Artsy this Pride Month 🏳️‍🌈

These past couple years, I have experienced multiple losses, betrayals, friendships and heartbreaks that have caused me deep pain and mistrust of others. It has not been easy. Sometimes I love too hard and care too much. It’s easy to forget about yourself and put yourself second. And it’s even more hard to realize that some people simply don’t have the best intentions for you. I have been working on healing through this, slowly. One day at a time and learning how to put myself first by embracing self-love. This quote rings true to me because sometimes “Part of healing is accepting that you might never fully understand what happened and that’s okay” ❤️‍🩹

I’ve had a total 3 artists copy and steal my ideas, and several handful “feel inspired.” This quote hits it on the right on head “Imitation isn’t flattery, it’s just annoying me.”

To me what is underestimated is that my artwork, concepts, and ideas are super personal and meaningful. I have spent many hours researching and generating them for my practice and what I do 🙅🏼‍♀️ This accounts both for my art practice and fashion. 

So next time, you “feel inspired,” jealous, or a zeal to steal. Maybe think for yourself and get your own! Instead of just checking out what your neighbour artist is doing, and then replicating it. 

Copying someone is not supporting 🙅🏻‍♀️
Glad to be living in 5D now 💫
